    • Field Detail

      • ownChartContainer

        private boolean ownChartContainer
        A boolean that indicates if this indicator has to be plotted in its own chart container, mainly because the values range is different than the values ranges of the data sources.

      • inputs

        private java.util.List<InputInfo> inputs
        The list of input sources.

      • parameters

        private java.util.List<ParameterInfo> parameters
        The list of parameters.

      • lookBackward

        private int lookBackward
        The necessary number of backward values to calculate the indicator, depends on the indicator implementation. If greater than zero, the system will call the calculate method after backward values are available.

      • lookForward

        private int lookForward
        The necessary number of forward values to calculate the indicator.
